  "texts": [
    "In this section we start studying the literature regarding the two research variables, namely requirements elicitation and culture.",
    "The emphasis is placed on the meaning and the role of culture in GSE.",
    "Particular focus is put on influences of culture on the requirements elicitation process.",
    "Increasingly GSE, also called Distributed Software Engineering, takes place mainly because organizations seek cost-effective alternatives (outsourcing) outside the boundaries of countries (Siakas and Siakas 2015).",
    "These decisions are motivated by various reasons with different benefits, such as potential costs reduction, access to certain professional skills, increased competitiveness, flexibility of hiring practices, risk mitigation related to labor and taxes, and possibility of expansion into new markets (Mighetti and Hadad 2016)."
  ]
}